New Africa Properties of Botswana Surges in First Trading Day

-- B y   J e r r y   B u n g u
-- 
2011-09-28T09:34:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/new-africa-properties-of-botswana-surges-in-first-trading-day.html
New Africa Properties Ltd.,
Botswana’s biggest property company by market value, surged 10
percent in its first trading day after listing on the southern
African nation’s bourse.  The stock was at 2.20 pula at 10 a.m. in Gaborone compared
with an offer price of 2 pula a share, Thapelo Tsheole, the
exchange’s business development manager, said in an interview.  “This is the biggest property listing the exchange has
ever registered in its history with 2.3 billion pula ($317
million) market capitalization,” Tsheole said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jerry Bungu in Gaborone at 
 jbungu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  